{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Pastry","content":["Grease a tart tin (Ø 28 cm) and set aside. Place butter, flour and salt in mixing bowl then chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>.","Add water and mix <nobr>50 sec\/<\/nobr>. Roll out on a floured surface (2-3 mm thick) and fit into tart tin. Prick base with a fork then cover and chill in fridge for at least 30 minutes. Meanwhile, preheat oven to 200°C.","Line pastry with baking paper and fill with baking beans then bake blind for 15 minutes (200°C). Meanwhile, prepare filling."]},{"title":"Filling","content":["Place cheese in mixing bowl and chop <nobr>9 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place onions, oil and ½ tsp salt in mixing bowl then chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then sauté <nobr>5 min\/100°C\/speed <\/nobr>. Spread softened onions onto prepared pastry base, forming a first layer.","Place beef mince, ½ tsp salt and pepper in mixing bowl then sauté <nobr>7 min\/100°C\/\/speed <\/nobr>. Arrange meat on top of onion layer then set aside while preparing white sauce."]},{"title":"White Sauce","content":["Place flour, butter, milk, salt and pepper in mixing bowl then cook <nobr>6 min\/90°C\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Spread sauce evenly over meat layer then sprinkle with reserved grated cheese. Bake for 40 minutes (200°C) until golden on top and bubbling at the edges. Serve warm - works well with a dressed salad."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Pastry","content":["85 g butter, cold, diced, plus extra for greasing","250 g plain flour, for dusting","1 tsp fine sea salt","100 g water, ice cold"]},{"title":"Filling","content":["100 g Gruyère cheese, cut in pieces","300 g onions, quartered","30 g olive oil","1 tsp fine sea salt","400 g beef mince","¼ tsp ground black pepper"]},{"title":"White Sauce","content":["40 g plain flour","40 g butter, diced","400 g milk","1 pinch fine sea salt","1 pinch ground black pepper"]}],"id":"r86469","imag